" Mike Land .xvimrc file for XVIM
" Mappings done through XCode Saved Under 'VIM'
" <C-M> Show Completion List (set it also as move down list as well)
" <C-J> Move Down Completion List (AutoSuggest)
" <C-K> Move Up Completion List (AutoSuggest)
" <C-P> Open Quickly (to emulate the VIM plugin ControlP)
" <C-N> Show/Hide Project Manager (to emulate nerdtree, use Ctrl-Option-` to move focus)

" Note <C-v> can be used to map ctrl key

" set options
set hlsearch

" Go to next tab, Go to previous tab
nnoremap gT :xccmd selectPreviousTab<CR>
nnoremap gt :xccmd selectNextTab<CR>

" Comment out lines selected, Comment out current line
vnoremap gcc :xccmd commentAndUncommentCurrentLines<CR> 
nnoremap gcc :xccmd commentAndUncommentCurrentLines<CR> 

" Comment out current and next line, Comment out current and previous line
nnoremap gcj :xccmd commentAndUncommentCurrentLines<CR>j:xccmd commentAndUncommentCurrentLines<CR>
nnoremap gck :xccmd commentAndUncommentCurrentLines<CR>k:xccmd commentAndUncommentCurrentLines<CR>

" Mapping to emulate surround.vim
vnoremap S" c""<esc>hp
vnoremap S( c()<esc>hp
vnoremap S[ c[]<esc>hp

" Mike Land Original Mappings
" puts println(
nnoremap <space>c iprintln()<esc>==$i

" remap esc
inoremap jk <esc>

" paste from 0 register Normal Mode and Visual Mode
nnoremap <space>v "0p
vnoremap <space>v dh"0p

" set up 2 blank lines above and below then current line and go to insert mode
nnoremap <space>o o<esc>yy3po

" shortcut to Home Row Global Marks
nnoremap <space>a `A
nnoremap <space>s `S
nnoremap <space>d `D
nnoremap <space>f `F

" next issue, previous issue
nnoremap <space>l :ni<CR>
nnoremap <space>h :pi<CR>

" jump 10 Lines Up/Down, Normal and Visual Mode
nnoremap <space>j 10j
nnoremap <space>k 10k 
vnoremap <space>j 10j
vnoremap <space>k 10k
